In Confluence 3.4, there is a lot more duplication in the alt text used by profile pictures and other icons in Confluence.

For example in the comment list on a page, the profile icon text says "User icon: mryall" right next my name, "Matt Ryall". A screen reader would hear "User icon mryall Matt Ryall". See the screenshot for how it looks in a visual browser in the user hover.

We should not include alternative text for user icons when it appears right next to the user's full name already. The icon is just decorative imagery for visual browsers and is redundant for browsers without images and screen readers.

