There was some confusion during testing CONFDEV-897 as to whether the 't' tooltip should appear on the Add menu's Attachment item.

It shouldn't, because 't' is for Viewing attachments, and even though Add Attachment is currently on the View Attachment screen it's a separate action that the user should associate with a different shortcut.

Also, if we had an Add Attachment shortcut it should be related to the Insert Attachment option from the RTE so that the user could get used to one shortcut for adding shortcuts in different contexts... although the Insert Attachment RTE item just inserts a link.

